<item>
            <title>[SPARK-25776] The disk write buffer size must be greater than 12.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-25776</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;font color=&quot;#205081&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;UnsafeSorterSpillWriter.java&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/font&gt;, when we write a record to a spill file wtih {{ &lt;font color=&quot;#205081&quot;&gt;void write(Object baseObject, long baseOffset, int recordLength, long keyPrefix&lt;/font&gt;)}}, &lt;font color=&quot;#205081&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;recordLength&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;/font&gt;and &lt;font color=&quot;#205081&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;keyPrefix&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;/font&gt;will be written the disk write buffer first, and these will take 12 bytes, so the disk write buffer size must be greater than 12.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If &lt;font color=&quot;#205081&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;diskWriteBufferSize&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;/font&gt;is 10, it will print this exception info:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: 10&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;em&gt;at org.apache.spark.util.collection.unsafe.sort.UnsafeSorterSpillWriter.writeLongToBuffer (UnsafeSorterSpillWriter.java:91)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;em&gt;at org.apache.spark.util.collection.unsafe.sort.UnsafeSorterSpillWriter.write(UnsafeSorterSpillWriter.java:123)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;em&gt;at org.apache.spark.util.collection.unsafe.sort.UnsafeExternalSorter.spillIterator(UnsafeExternalSorter.java:498)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;em&gt;at org.apache.spark.util.collection.unsafe.sort.UnsafeExternalSorter.spill(UnsafeExternalSorter.java:222)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;em&gt;at org.apache.spark.memory.MemoryConsumer.spill(MemoryConsumer.java:65)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
